6.   GOVERNING LAW AND DISPUTE RESOLUTION
     6.1. This License shall be governed by the substantive laws of
          Sweden, without reference to its conflict of laws principles.
     6.2. Any disputes arising from the use of the Program shall first
          be resolved through negotiation between the parties, acting
          in good faith.
     6.3. If negotiation does not result in agreement within 60 days,
          either party may submit the dispute to arbitration in
          Stockholm, Sweden, administered by the Arbitration Institute
          of the Stockholm Chamber of Commerce (SCC). The arbitration
          shall be conducted in English.
     6.4. Disputes involving claims of a value less than €10,000 may,
          at the claimant's discretion, be brought before the ordinary
          courts of Stockholm rather than arbitration.
     6.5. If the entity using the Program is domiciled in a jurisdiction
          where enforcement of this License would be impractical or
          impossible due to local laws, that entity shall make a good
          faith effort to find an equivalent legal basis to honor the
          terms of this License. Failure to do so may result in
          termination of rights under this License.

